{
  "texts": [
    "This includes two variants of EconRoBERTa-Large, with EconRoBERTapre denoting the model trained solely on the EA dataset.",
    "For LLMs, fine-tuning is implemented on a single model using hierarchical prompts, employing the QLoRA technique [18] to manage GPU memory constraints.",
    "The RoBERTa-Large [16] and FinBERT [44] models are fine-tuned to establish a baseline for non-LLM performance, while the zero-shot results serve as the baseline for LLMs.",
    "Training Pre TrainingTo establish a robust foundation for economic language understanding, we pre-trained a RoBERTa Base model exclusively on the EA dataset (refer to Section 3.1.1).",
    "This pretraining process involved a learning rate of 5e-4 and spanned 10 epochs, using an A100 GPU with 80 GB of memory over a period of 20 days, using the same amount of electricity required to self-drive an electric car for 1000 km."
  ]
}